{"at":805852804.628294,"ticketId":"29","id":"29-1337","detail":"thinking: ## DECOMPOSE Report — Issue #29: Create the `language_tiers` package\n\n### 1. Module Identity\n- **Module path**: `github.com\/iksnae\/code-certification` (from `go.mod`)\n- **Go version**: 1.25.5\n\n### 2. The `analysis.ForLanguage` dependency — exactly what it does\n\nDefined at **`internal\/analysis\/analyzer.go:182-183`**:\n\n```go\nfunc ForLanguage(lang string) Analyzer {\n    if factory, ok := registry[lang]; ok {\n        return factory()\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\nIt looks up a private `registry` map. The registry is populated by `init()` functions in each language-analyzer file:\n\n| Language key | File | Init line |\n|---|---|---|\n| `\"go\"` | `internal\/analysis\/go_analyzer.go` | `init()` line ~22 |\n| `\"ts\"` | `internal\/analysis\/ts_analyzer.go` | `init()` line ~19 |\n| `\"js\"` | `internal\/analysis\/ts_analyzer.go` | `init()` line ~20 (same grammar subset) |\n| `\"py\"` | `internal\/analysis\/python_analyzer.go` | `init()` line ~16 |\n| `\"rs\"` | `internal\/analysis\/rust_analyzer.go` | `init()` line ~15 |\n\nAny other language string — `\"ruby\"`, `\"swift\"`, `\"c\"`, `\"\"` — returns **nil**.\n\n### 3. What must be created\n\n**Two new files in a new directory** (doesn't exist yet):\n\n- **`internal\/language_tiers\/language_tiers.go`** — new package `language_tiers`\n  - A `Tier` type (int-based, with `const` block)\n  - Constants: `TierGeneric` (iota), `TierFull`\n  - Function: `TierForLanguage(lang string) Tier` — calls `analysis.ForLanguage(lang)`, returns `TierFull` if non-nil, `TierGeneric` otherwise\n\n- **`internal\/language_tiers\/language_tiers_test.go`** — table-driven test\n  - TierFull cases: `\"go\"`, `\"ts\"`, `\"py\"`, `\"rs\"`, `\"js\"`\n  - TierGeneric cases: `\"ruby\"`, `\"swift\"`, `\"c\"`, `\"\"`\n\n### 4. Existing code that already uses `analysis.ForLanguage` (not to modify)\n- `internal\/engine\/certifier.go:183` — `analyzer := analysis.ForLanguage(lang)`\n- `internal\/discovery\/analysis_adapter.go:32` — `analyzer: analysis.ForLanguage(lang)`\n\nThese already handle nil (no analyzer) gracefully; the new package is purely additive.\n\n### 5. Test conventions observed\n- All tests in this repo use the standard `testing` package (no testify, no ginkgo)\n- Table-driven tests are idiomatic (see `TestGoAnalyzer_ToEvidence_HasAllMetrics` for a loop-over-cases pattern)\n- Package-names match directory names; tests are in the same package (e.g., `package analysis`)\n\n### 6. Non-goals (confirmed absent from scope)\n- ❌ Do not modify `scorer.go`, `pipeline.go`, or any report files\n- ❌ Do not add `Unsupported` field to `CertificationRecord`\n- ❌ Do not change `Score()` signature\n\n### 7. Verification\n- **Command**: `go test .\/... -count=1` — all existing tests pass, new package compiles and tests pass\n\n### 8. Implementation summary for next phase (PLAN)\n\n| What | Where | How |\n|---|---|---|\n| `Tier` type + constants | `internal\/language_tiers\/language_tiers.go` | `type Tier int; const (TierGeneric Tier = iota; TierFull)` |\n| `TierForLanguage` | same file | Import `analysis`, call `analysis.ForLanguage(lang)`, return TierFull\/TierGeneric |\n| Table-driven test | `internal\/language_tiers\/language_tiers_test.go` | 9 cases: 5 TierFull, 4 TierGeneric, in a `[]struct` loop |","phase":"decompose","outcome":{"note":{}}}
